<subSubSection id="4BF7A785FD4E8C3E030C8805A8483F5A" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="ecology and distribution">
<paragraph id="C3A71887BC69D0C56E22E674CAE99617" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Ecology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E06624B3103864EF92AE2D16E7B39B5" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Terrestrial plant on clayey rocky soils on the peaks of the highland summits of the Pirhuani peak, near Tassa town, Moquegua Region, at elevations of 4650-4700 m. It occurs with 
<taxonomicName id="5561290B4A398119CED4805470C79707" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Azorella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0908E12A46DB154731A463F44AF427F2" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Azorella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4D16D8E61353E7EB9ED063C124D7EA08" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Poaceae" genus="Calamagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Graminales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54F3D51B0D8FC2D3737D2A735652CB02" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Calamagrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CA24EF6179358E6906372BB5E0D6F0F9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Pycnophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49AB71D5EF59140D66CBBBAA2A7B862C" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Pycnophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7288D441E1198234A114BD6A0073A529" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Mniodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="76084789575FF40D80E8D4D68A0A31BB" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mniodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CBD88E93DB84DCEF22C05A56954C7C10" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B730A5FC53662C8D58C3727FF759E212" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="3A5719F9C564538E8303A54743BA6701" authorityName="V.A.Funk" authorityYear="1997" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Xenophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AE4A670707B8CAF85683993E02FAA277" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Xenophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Flowers and fruits between March and April.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="533CABD831B21942CC6808646F15ACE8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3998D115284F7FFFF8FF5BEB2D025E6D" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED67A1E0A9FAC79B51FA3BA528AD8C08" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
This 
<taxonomicName id="FB71A478174E23F57A6F60B457C8D427" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="379CA23CEAE92222BCD6C9CF07EC85B8" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named after the town of Tassa (Moquegua Region), downslope of Pirhuani peak where the species was found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB78034EA26AD51BC91B39D6C8B834AA" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D306503A43077C5A3F5F25C70775604F" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C080D9CE964BF5F31505EB1B797F736C" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="6EF2CC234715B88F00654E5123F2B61A" authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tassaensis">
<emphasis id="01A75D0EC02F091BB8B9862226C24077" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio tassaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="9B2CB1158957A7FAEA5D9090ED7FE4EE" authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moqueguensis">
<emphasis id="B77B53E6D647FBD0FAF9F986E389C5B9" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio moqueguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which grows at the same elevational range but approaches the known range of 
<taxonomicName id="B45B127D85BD0F062BE5B899C6DCFDFC" authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tassaensis">
<emphasis id="C51D7538E0AE902C34A6ABA0A02A59AA" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio tassaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within a few hundred metres. 
<taxonomicName id="0BBCF8242F4B063DEF0ADB8C4FF2DD7D" authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moqueguensis">
<emphasis id="F57A652393A73BA86415A05E05280DBA" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio moqueguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is generally distinctive in the series for its larger size, attaining dense ground mats, and for its yellow corolla. 
<taxonomicName id="9D546FDB00BF24299BF32E16D12DF9BA" authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tassaensis">
<emphasis id="CCA8724BD80C58FD3E67EA4AEFA20FB3" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio tassaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 12-16 phyllaries (vs. 9-12), an involucre length of 6-8 mm and achene length of 1-1.2 mm, being much shorter than in 
<taxonomicName id="C33487C312140CEDD4B0F70E6B371F7D" authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moqueguensis">
<emphasis id="F4C88C6D2E9CEC7820D957C63DBD7044" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio moqueguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="7C3DAFD1D72B5E3638C3A888DE087C21" authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tassaensis">
<emphasis id="E1E83F9DCBF35E1A254C3C4EB9E6E8A4" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio tassaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is relatively a very rare species with an estimated 100 individuals known. It is less similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2F6CB77A1894B47E697AA45F886C8231" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pucapampaensis">
<emphasis id="75EB4945DE264699B3183AA0A6008C45" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio pucapampaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="14A5DC9DF783C69E07FC712D80DE759C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="evacoides">
<emphasis id="AD769BCDACFBAC23251C34DBA77193A3" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio evacoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AC07A09C0DE0D4C0A62C64BEE8CFAC7A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="expansus">
<emphasis id="9EDEE5FD85D14C055E1FC79E1516AD1E" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio expansus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ECBF58AAFB81E798E34408EFDB50D16C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis id="541CF310A425CE206463F505E81B80EA" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and can be distinguished on the basis of the habit, trichomes, leaf shape and length, calycular bracts and phyllaries length and shape as summarized in 
<tableCitation id="48C4787E87B9FF2D5D8CE4B1D0B5551C" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Comparison between Senecio moqueguensis, Senecio sykorae, Senecio tassaensis and their closest relatives." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/8C880042D6329C0A9CC8A11354D89ACE" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" tableUuid="8C880042D6329C0A9CC8A11354D89ACE">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1463AE4FF1849CFA2D38C009981DB48A" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="9503267869656EE183C3DDB32FC1FEBC" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3FD1851B0CD57EC1DFDA6D8ACC1077E4" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Following the criteria and categories of 
<bibRefCitation id="0E991017BF880ED6ED1DDF71F6478CF7" author="IUCN," journalOrPublisher="Darwiniana" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="B10" refString="IUCN, , 2001. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second Edition. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second Edition. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, a preliminary status of Critically Endangered (CR) is assigned. The new species deserves protection because its total area of occupancy is less than 10 km² (ca. 5 km²) (B2); only one population is known (B2b); habitat inferred to be continuing to decline(B2b(i-iii)); population estimated to number fewer than 100 individuals (D). The suitable habitats for 
<taxonomicName id="E8E4C041031FAF553E4B7E85ABE25B60" authorityName="Montesinos" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tassaensis">
<emphasis id="368BFA9690C82107BAC9286717F724A1" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Senecio tassaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the mountain summits of Pirhuani peak in the Ubinas district are indicated as endangered, because changes in the annual rainfall, volcanic activity and exploitation of natural resources, may all reduce their extent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
